**Quality Assurance and Quality Improvement Specialist Position Description**

We're seeking a Quality Assurance and Quality Improvement (QA/QI) Specialist to join our Bronx team. The QA/QI Specialist will engage in ongoing quality assurance and quality improvement work related to our community programs. These programs currently consist of the Bronx HYPE Family Enrichment Center (FEC) and the Haven and Hope School-Based Early Support Program. The QA/QI Specialist will work directly with program directors and leaders to ensure program model and goals are being met, and a quarterly QA/QI cycle is in place to ensure ongoing improvement. This role is ideal for someone who is highly organized, proficient in Excel and Google Sheets, skilled at developing surveys and data collection methods, and can independent problem solve and develop actionable next steps. The QA/QI Specialist makes data-based decisions and recommendations, and supports programs in implementing these recommendations.

**Title:** Quality Assurance and Quality Improvement (QA/QI) Specialist

**Salary/Pay:** $25-$30 per hour Non-Exempt

**Job Type:** Hourly/Non-Exempt

**Work Location:** 111 Bruckner Blvd, Bronx, NY 10454

**Work Hours:** 25-30 hours per week

**Preferred Schedule:** Tuesdays and Thursdays 10:00am-3:30pm; Wednesdays and Fridays 10:00am-6:00pm; Up to One Saturday per month 12:00pm-3:00pm (There is some schedule flexibility)

**Specific responsibilities include but are not limited to:**

* Visits programs to engage in conversations and interactions with the purpose of building rapport and strengthening relationships;
* Represents the organization and conduct outreach at community events and venues;
* Delivers presentations of data and quality improvement outcomes at external and internal meetings;
* Develops, leads and maintains a quarterly quality improvement cycle involving data collection, data analysis and recommended next steps;
* Leads the implementation of quality improvement recommendations and ensures recommendations are implemented;
* Ensures a clear and thorough understanding of program model, program goals and contract requirements;
* Develops, implements and maintains specific systems for the evaluation and improvement of programs;
* Maintains records and continually monitors program components that are key to the program model;
* Uses program goals to establish specific criteria and standards for highest achievable program quality;
* Sets clear quality improvement expectations for program leaders;
* Communicates feedback and next steps positively and constructively;
* Conducts regularly scheduled analyses of program operations and systems to identify areas of need and recommended next steps;
* Takes initiative in developing and implementing new systems and procedures aimed at improving program quality or efficiency;
* Creates and facilitates workshops and trainings for program leaders and staff to introduce new systems or improve current systems;
* Identifies success measures and evaluates effectiveness of Parent Advisory Board (PAC), offerings, community co-designing approach, community engagement strategies, and staff professional development;
* Engages in data tracking and analysis, and compiling written reports for external stakeholders;
* Develops surveys and data collection methods;
* Creates toolkits, guides and resources;
* Performs other duties as assigned.

**Minimum Qualifications**

* Baccalaureate Degree and at least two (2) years of professional experience in QA/QI
* Excellent writing and speaking skills
* Excellent analytical skills

**Preferred Qualifications**

* Bilingual (Spanish and English);
* At least three (3) years of experience living and/or working in the Bronx;
* At least two (2) years of experience working with children and families;
* Outstanding communication, interpersonal and organizational skills;
* Knowledge and experience working in the Mott Haven/Melrose Community.

Submission of a resume is not a guarantee that you will receive an interview. Only those candidates under consideration will be contacted.

