**INTRODUCTION**

The Assistant Program Manager provides oversight and management of daily operations in conjunction with the Program Manager of the Midland Day Habilitation program. The Assistant Program Manager reports directly to the Program Manager. This person is responsible to provide supervision, training and evaluation of the Community Specialists in overseeing programs that help individuals with disabilities improve life and social skills.

**RESPONSIBILITIES**

* Serve as a resource to all day habilitation staff; assuming supervision in the absence of the Program Manager;
* In the absence of the Program Manager participate in Interdisciplinary Team meetings and Service Plan meetings for all program participants;
* Assist and develop policies with Program Manager;
* Train Community Specialists on their required documentation including but not limited to; Progress Notes, Incident Reports, etc.;
* Observe, evaluate and supervise Community Specialists in all of their responsibilities;
* Assist staff in providing proactive, positive measures/techniques to encourage appropriate behaviors;
* Monitor for program compliance with all stakeholders. Quality assurance of personnel files for employees and all files (electronic and paper) for individuals served;
* Represent Midland at local business functions;
* Order, inventory and maintenance of programmatic supplies;
* Completion of all required Division of Developmental Disabilities (DDD) reports for program participants;
* Provide back up to Community Specialists;
* Perform attendance count for simulated and non-simulated emergencies;
* Work collaboratively with all Midland staff;
* Required to stay late for occasional events;
* Ensure all work including but not limited to, progress notes are completed within the required time frame;
* Fill in for Community Specialists and Nurse when there are absences;
* Maintain daily Activity Schedule and staff assignments;
* Perform all other duties as assigned by the Program Manager and Assistant Director of Employment and Day Services.

**Requirements**

* High School Diploma (or equivalent), Bachelor’s degree preferred;
* Prior Experience (minimum of one (1) year) with the intellectually and/or developmentally disabled population is preferred;
* Also achieved with three (3) years of mgmt.. in I/DD program w/ Associate’s Degree; or
* Five (5) years of mgmt.. in I/DD program w/ HS Diploma;
* Valid Driver’s License with a clean driving record;
* NJ Criminal Background Clearance;
* Must be willing to complete all required Division of Developmental Disabilities trainings and successfully maintain the required CEUs throughout their tenure;
* Intermediate to Advanced PC skills with proficiency in:

MS Office including MS Word, Excel, Outlook and PowerPoint;

* Human Services software;
* Ability to maintain a high level of confidentiality;
* Must have high initiative, integrity, strong work ethic, good communication and analytical skills;
* Excellent time management, organizational skills and enjoy working in a fast paced environment;
* Able and willing to work well in a diverse environment.

**Physical Demands**

The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of the job. Reasonable accommodation may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

* Ability to sit/stand for extended periods;
* Ability to lift/move up to 50 lbs.

